24/04/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The Socialist Party and the Democratic Alliance Party signed a co-operation agreement Wednesday (23 April) about the fall local elections. 
The two parties are members of the ruling coalition, Alliance for the State. 
They agreed to nominate joint candidates and, in some areas, may offer joint platforms. 
Party leaders also said they hope to boost co-operation within the coalition at government and parliamentary levels. 
(Shekulli - 24/04/03; ATA, Albanian radio - 23/04/03)
